"Hammitt J.K., Jain A.K., Adams J.L., Wuebbles D.J.","A welfare-based index for assessing environmental effects of greenhouse-gas emissions",1996,"Nature","381","6580",,"301","303",,,10.1038/381301a0,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0029667598&partnerID=40&md5=ff8f9a9d29ffc964a74deaeca6e6f0d8","Center for Risk Analysis, Dept. of Health Policy and Mangement, Harvard School of Public Health, 718 Huntington Avenue, Boston, MA 02115, United States; Department of Atmospheric Sciences, University of Illinois, 105 South Gregory Avenue, Urbana, IL 61801, United States; RAND Corporation, 1700 Main Street, Santa Monica, CA 90407, United States","Hammitt, J.K., Center for Risk Analysis, Dept. of Health Policy and Mangement, Harvard School of Public Health, 718 Huntington Avenue, Boston, MA 02115, United States; Jain, A.K., Department of Atmospheric Sciences, University of Illinois, 105 South Gregory Avenue, Urbana, IL 61801, United States; Adams, J.L., RAND Corporation, 1700 Main Street, Santa Monica, CA 90407, United States; Wuebbles, D.J., Department of Atmospheric Sciences, University of Illinois, 105 South Gregory Avenue, Urbana, IL 61801, United States","The global warming potential (GWP) index is a measure of the relative contribution of the emissions of different greenhouse gases to the radiative forcing of the atmosphere - and thus to climate change - over a given time period. But this index does not represent the effects of climate change, and therefore does not provide an adequate basis for policy decisions about emissions reductions. This inadequacy has led to the proposal of an alternative, the economic-damage index (EDI). This index compares the effect of different greenhouse-gas emissions on global economic welfare. Here we use a simple climate model to calculate the EDIs for a range of climate-change/greenhouse-gas emission scenarios, and compare the values to the corresponding GWPs. Although the values of these indices are, at this stage, broadly similar in both magnitude and uncertainty, the prospects of reducing these uncertainties by future research are better for the EDI.",,"article; atmosphere; climate; economic aspect; environmental impact assessment; experimental model; gas waste; greenhouse effect; policy; priority journal; radiation; welfare; climate change; climate modelling; economic damage index; emission reduction; global warming potential index; greenhouse gas",,,,,,"Shine, K.P., Derwent, R.G., Wuebbles, D.J., Morcrette, J.-J., (1990) Climate Change: The IPCC Scientific Assessment, pp. 41-68. , (eds Houghton, J. T., Jenkins, G J. & Ephraums, J. J.) Cambridge Univ. Press; Isaksen, I.S.A., Ramaswamy, V., Rodhe, H., Wigley, T.M.L., (1992) Climate Change 1992: The Supplementary Report to the IPCC Scientific Assessment, pp. 47-67. , (eds Houghton, J. T., Callander, B. A. & Varney, S. K.) Cambridge Univ. Press; Albritton, D.L., Derwent, R.G., Isaksen, I.S.A., Lal, M., Wuebbles, D.J., (1995) Climate Change 1994: Radiative Forcing of Climate Change and an Evaluation of the IPCC IS92 Emissions Scenarios, pp. 205-231. , (eds Houghton, J. T. et al.) Cambridge Univ. Press; Eckaus, R.S., (1992) Energy J, 13, pp. 25-35; Reilly, J.M., Richards, K.R., (1993) Envir. Resourc. Econ., 3, pp. 41-61; Schmalensee, R., (1993) Energy J, 14, pp. 245-255; Kandlikar, M., (1995) Energy Policy, 23, pp. 879-883; Cropper, M.L., Oates, W.E., (1992) J. Econ. Literat., 30, pp. 675-740; Victor, D.G., (1991) Policy Sci., 24, pp. 199-222; Lashof, D.A., Ahuja, D.R., (1990) Nature, 344, pp. 529-531; Hammitt, J.K., Lempert, R.J., Schlesinger, M.E., (1992) Nature, 357, pp. 315-318; Wuebbles, D.J., Jain, A.K., Patten, K.O., Grant, K.E., (1995) Clim. Change, 29, pp. 265-297; Nordhaus, W.D., (1992) Science, 258, pp. 1315-1319; Peck, S.C., Teisberg, T.J., (1992) Energy J., 13, pp. 55-77; Manne, A., Mendelsohn, R., Richels, R., (1995) Energy Policy, 23, pp. 17-34; Leggett, J., Pepper, W., Swart, R., (1992) Climate Change 1992: The Supp